cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about optimizing hyperparameters for artificial neural networks (ANNs) in natural language processing tasks, specifically for dialog act classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian processes (GPs) for optimization, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing ANNs, which is a sub-field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of GPs for optimization also falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses reducing computational time, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
